  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, we also used a pretrained model on the Microsoft Common Objects in Context (MS COCO) dataset to improve the training efficiency of YOLOX.",
    "The epoch value was an important hyperparameter for the training of the YOLOX network.",
    "An epoch value that is too small could lead to underfitting of the model, while an epoch value that is too large could lead to overfitting of the model.",
    "The relationship between the loss values and the epoch values during the training of the YOLOX model is given in Supplementary Fig. 18.",
    "In addition, the other two localization networks, including Faster R-CNN 33 and RetinaNet 34, were further separately trained on the CXR-AL14 dataset."
